definitions.definition: Part of or similar to rhetoric , the use of language as a means to persuade.
examples: A rhetorical question is one used merely to make a point, with no response expected.

definitions.definition: Not earnest , or presented only for the purpose of an argument.

main_definition: Part of or similar to rhetoric , the use of language as a means to persuade.
secondary_definitions: Not earnest , or presented only for the purpose of an argument.
